  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Objective The objective is to compare the efficacy of spironolactone and eplerenone on
      clinical outcome in patients with heart failure and a reduced ejection fraction.

      Method The study is a crossover cluster randomized trial. Each heart failure clinic in
      Denmark will be allocated to four periods (clusters): two periods with spironolactone and two
      periods with eplerenone as first drug. The planned total participation time for each
      department is 4 years and we estimate that data from 7200 patients will be accrued in this
      period. Endpoints will be assessed through Danish National Registries.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
